    <body>
        <div xml:id="AN25-kilavi"></div>
        <div xml:id="AN25">
            <lg type="edition"><l>neṭuṅkaraik <choice><seg>kāṉiyāṟṟuk</seg><seg>kāṉyāṟṟuk</seg></choice> kaṭumpuṉal cāa</l>
<l>yaviraṟal koṇṭa viravumaṇa lakaṉṟuṟait</l>
<l>taṇkaya naṇṇiya poḻiṟoṟuṅ kāñcip</l>
<l>paintā taṇinta pōtumali yekkar</l>
<l>vatuvai nāṟṟam putuvatu kañala</l>
<l><choice><seg>mānaṉai</seg><seg>māṉaṉai</seg></choice> koḻutiya maṇiniṟa viruṅkuyil</l>
<l>paṭunā viḷiyā <choice><seg>ṉīṭuniṉ</seg><seg>ṉaṭuniṉ</seg></choice> ṟal<supplied>ka</supplied>lu</l>
<l>muraippa pōla vūḻkoḷpu <supplied>nu</supplied>vala</l>
<l><choice><seg>viḷaccita</seg><seg>viṉaiccita</seg></choice> rukutta vilavat tāṅkaṭ</l>
<l>ciṉaippūṅ kō<supplied>ṅ</supplied>ki ṉuṇṭātu pakarnar</l>
<l>pavaḻac ceppiṟ poṉcorin taṉṉa</l>
<l>vikaḻuna rikaḻā viḷanā ḷamaiyañ</l>
<l>ceytōr maṉṟa kuṟiyeṉa <choice><seg>nīriṉ</seg><seg>nīniṉ</seg></choice></l>
<l><choice><seg>maika</seg><seg>paita</seg></choice> luṇkaṇ paṉivār puṟaippa</l>
<l>vārā maiyiṟ pulanta neñcamoṭu</l>
<l><choice><seg>nōvaraṟ</seg><seg>nōvaṟ</seg></choice> kuṟumaka ṇōyiyareṉ ṉuyireṉa</l>
<l>melliya viṉiya kūṟi vallē</l>
<l>varuvar vāḻi tōḻi <choice><seg>poruvar</seg><seg>porunar</seg></choice></l>
<l>celcamaṅ kaṭanta vilkeḻu taṭakkaip</l>
<l>potiyiṟ celvaṉ <choice><seg>polantārt</seg><seg>polantērt</seg></choice> titiya</l>
<l>ṉiṉṉicai yiyattiṟ kaṟaṅkuṅ</l>
<l><choice><seg>kaṉmukai</seg><seg>kaṉmicai</seg></choice> yaruviya kāṭiṟan tōrē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“While the fast flood of the long-shored forest river is exhausted,</l>
<l>[and] what is new is dense with wedding fragrance</l>
<l>in the dunes abounding in buds adorned with fresh pollen</l>
<l>of the Portia trees in every grove close to the cool depth</l>
<l>of the wide ghat with [white] sand mixed with shining black sand,</l>
<l>while the sapphire-coloured big koels that pecked at the big buds</l>
<l>call, [all] taking [their] turn as if they were <choice><seg>talking</seg><seg>talking,</seg></choice> </l>
<l><choice><seg>all night, staying long with </seg><seg>intervening all night by </seg></choice> the sound of [their] moving tongues,</l>
<l>those who announce the fresh pollen<note place="foot">nuṇ tāṭu pakarnar: here the honorific shows that we are dealing with a reference to people, most likely the flower-selling women, a minor topos of the spring season, found more explicitly for example in NA 97.</note> of cameg from flowers on branches</l>
<l rend="indent">	there on the silk-cotton trees that <choice><seg>young </seg><seg>busy </seg></choice> bees had shed,</l>
<l rend="indent">	negligent as if gold had been poured from a coral vessel,</l>
<l>without being negligent have indeed taken the opportunity</l>
<l>of the young day. [It is] a sign<note place="foot">It is as well possible to construe differently and read kuṟi as the direct object of ceytōr: “on the occasion of the young day they have given a sign”.</note>”</l>
<l rend="indent"> – <choice><seg>so </seg><seg>as you </seg></choice> <choice><seg>saying,</seg><seg>say so,</seg></choice> </l>
<l><choice><seg>little woman who is undergoing pain,</seg><seg>don’t you ache, little woman,</seg></choice> </l>
<l>with a heart vexed because of [his] not coming</l>
<l>so that dew overflows [and] drips from <choice><seg>[your] </seg><seg>your suffering </seg></choice> collyrium <choice><seg>eyes, black stones in water,</seg><seg>eyes.</seg></choice> </l>
<l><choice><seg></seg><seg>Saying: “let my life suffer”, </seg></choice> talking soft [and] sweet <choice><seg>[words] to say “let my life suffer”</seg><seg>[words]</seg></choice> </l>
<l>he will come quickly, oh friend,</l>
<l>– the one who traversed the wilderness of waterfalls <choice><seg>in </seg><seg>on </seg></choice> <choice><seg>stone caves</seg><seg>stony heights</seg></choice> </l>
<l>that resound <choice><seg>like </seg><seg>with </seg></choice> the sweet-sounding instruments</l>
<l>of Titiyaṉ with a golden <choice><seg>garland, </seg><seg>chariot, </seg></choice> the lord of Potiyil,</l>
<l>[his] broad hands holding a bow, who overcame [his] enemies in moving battle.</l>
<l rend="indent"></l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
